Results of all testing undertaken should be recorded. Such records may be used as evidence that mandatory testing was carried out, and may be used for comparison with later tests results.
Test records should include:
(a) identification of the circuit (s) tested;
(b) the tests undertaken;
(c) the results of those tests;
(d) the identity of the person who carried out the testing; and
(e) the date.
Test records should be kept for a minimum of 5 years.
NOTE Legislative requirements may be made in each State or Territory of Australia or New Zealand relating to the format and contents of test records.
